description:
The daughter company of Berlin electronic publishing Directmedia Publishing GmbH http://www.directmedia.de/ - founded in 2001. 

The main activities Directmedia Publishing GmbH - the publication of artistic and scientific literature, reference books, dictionaries and illustrated books on art on CD-ROM. 

From 1997 Directmedia Publishing GmbH and Ltd. "Directmedia Publishing" published more than 250 CD-ROM, totaling more than 4 million pages. On the disk contains more than 13 000 books 2000 authors. Published by collaborating with leading publishers in the world, such as "Brockhaus", "Reklam", "Verlag CHBeck", "Taschenbuch", "Eksmo," Avanta + "," Logos "and many others. The authors of our publications - known to art historians and specialists. 

Directmedia Publishing GmbH is one of the first electronic publishing, focusing on high standards for publishing electronic books. When buying our products, you get no text or database, and electronic books that pleasure to read and which is convenient to operate. The electronic books and CDs of our publishers realized all the details of publishing design, built up in book publishing for centuries. Publishing quality and specially designed software made DirektMedia the market leader in Germany and Europe.
